Unlike other easy-to-use web tools for IVR, it was designed for building speech applications from the ground up by people who had been designing speech applications for years. In addition to having an easy-to-use web interface, some of the key features include built-in audio libraries for high quality playback of dates, times, and numbers. Built-in steps for menu items. Built-in reprompt and error handling to simplify handling input errors for speech recognition. The easiest way to get familiar with it is to start by loading a template and playing with the values in the template. When you're ready to start building your own app, first build your call flow on paper, then you will be able to very quickly implement it using Designer. Please enjoy the rest of this demo project by exploring data capture and trying out some of our demo applications.]]></ttstext></static-audio><static-audio id="71df6d01-4a5c-445c-9f15-eb575fd01d3d" filename="captureintro.wav"><ttstext><![CDATA[Designer makes it easy to capture different kinds of input from your caller.
